--------------------------------------------------
bundle.min.js can be recreated/updated using gulp.
Or simple take my (zvolsky/) bundle.min.js and check if it works for you.
--------------------------------------------------
IDEA:
You should edit package.json,
then: npm install
and: gulp build
(you can then move bundle.min.js + .js.map into your "production" copy of django-jet)

DETAIL:
npm i -g gulp-cli
npm i -g npm-check-updates
# in django-jet/ root (where package.json is located)
ncu -u   # writes latest versions into packages.json (except of packages installed from github)
# fix packages where update to the latest version will cause a failure
npm install
npm audit
npm audit fix
# some final tweaks - see troubleshouting
gulp build      # now for Gulp 4.x
